@page
@model Nerdnest.Pages.Clas.IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Online school";
}

<div class="container-fluid classes">
    <div class="container text-center">
        <br />
        <h1 style="text-decoration: underline;">
            Physics
        </h1>
        <br />
        <h3>
            Why you should take Assembly Course?
        </h3>
        <br />
        <p class="mb-5">
            Assembly language provides a low-level view of computer architecture and how computers execute instructions. By learning assembly language, you gain a deeper understanding of how processors work, how memory is accessed, and how instructions are executed.
        </p>

    </div>
    <table class="container my-5" width="100%">
        <tr>
            <th>
                <img src="~/assets/assembly1.jpg" width="600px" style="border-radius: 15px;" />
            </th>
            <th>
                <h5 style="text-align:center;" class="mr-5">Embedded Systems Programming:</h5>
                <p style="width: 100%;text-align:right;" class="my-5">

                    Assembly language is commonly used in embedded systems programming, where memory and processing power are limited. Many microcontrollers and embedded devices require programming in assembly language to achieve the necessary level of performance and efficiency.
                </p>
            </th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <th>
                <h5 style="text-align:left;" class="mr-5">Security Research:</h5>
                <p style="width: 100%;text-align: left;" class="my-5">
                    Security researchers and analysts often use assembly language to analyze and exploit software vulnerabilities. Understanding assembly language is essential for understanding the behavior of malware, identifying security vulnerabilities, and developing effective security countermeasures.
                </p>
            </th>
            <th>
                <img src="~/assets/assembly2.jpg" width="500px" style="border-radius: 15px; margin-left: 20%" />
            </th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <th>
                <img src="~/assets/assembly3.png" width="500px" style="border-radius: 15px;" />
            </th>
            <th>
                <h5 style="text-align:center;" class="my-5">Reverse Engineering:</h5>
                <p style="width: 100%;text-align:right;" class="my-5">
                    Knowledge of assembly language is valuable for reverse engineering software and understanding how programs are implemented at a low level. Reverse engineers use assembly language to analyze executable code, understand its behavior, and identify security vulnerabilities or performance bottlenecks.
                </p>
            </th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <th>
                <h5 style="text-align:left;" class="mr-5">Career Advancement: </h5>
                <p style="width: 100%;text-align: left;" class="my-5">
                    Proficiency in assembly language can set you apart in the job market and open up opportunities for specialized roles in areas such as embedded systems development, systems programming, security research, and firmware engineering. Employers value candidates who have a deep understanding of computer architecture and low-level programming concepts.
                </p>
            </th>
            <th>
                <img src="~/assets/assembly4.jpg" width="500px" style="border-radius: 15px; margin-left: 20%" />
            </th>
        </tr>
    </table>
    <br /><br />
    <div class="container">
        <button class="btn btn-primary col-12" style="height: 50px; font-size: 20px;">Take the course</button>
    </div><br /><br /><br />


</div>